-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-rc-dangerholm-dream-build-pearl-white-super-lightweight-xc-bike-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-rc-dangerholm-dream-build-pearl-white-super-lightweight-xc-bike-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-rc-dangerholm-dream-build-pearl-white-super-lightweight-xc-bike-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-rc-dangerholm-dream-build-pearl-white-super-lightweight-xc-bike-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a>There were three final iterations of Dangerholm’s Hyper Spark, each with its own seat post and saddle combination. The lightest of the three runs a one-piece Berk combo with no rails – that’s the black one pictured above that weighs in at 133g.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-white-seat-post-saddle-integrated.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-white-seat-post-saddle-integrated.jpg\" alt=\"scott hyperspark white schmolke carbon seat post\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-white-seat-post-saddle-integrated.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-white-seat-post-saddle-integrated.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-white-seat-post-saddle-integrated-297x223.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netd