-white-seat-post-saddle-integrated-768x576.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-white-seat-post-saddle-integrated-696x522.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-white-seat-post-saddle-integrated-1068x801.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-white-seat-post-saddle-integrated-560x420.jpg 560w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-white-seat-post-saddle-integrated-80x60.jpg 80w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-white-seat-post-saddle-integrated-265x198.jpg 265w\"></a></p><p>The white is the one-piece Berk combo with a Schmolke carbon seat post and rails added for flex and comfort. It weighs 183g. The third and final iteration was the heaviest, running a RockShox Reverb AXS 170mm dropper seat post, with the complete bike weighing in at 10.5 kg.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build.jpg\" alt=\"scott hyperspark damgerholm build\" width=\"960\" height=\"1200\" sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build.jpg 960w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build-240x300.jpg 240w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build-800x1000.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build-96x120.jpg 96w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build-768x960.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build-696x870.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build-336x420.jpg 336w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build.jpg 960w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build-240x300.jpg 240w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build-800x1000.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build-96x120.jpg 96w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build-768x960.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build-696x870.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/scott-hyper-spark-dangerholm-white-build-336x420.jpg 336w\"></a></p><p>As usual, Dangerholm has left nothing to chance with the Hyper Spark build. Every single detail has been painstakingly pored over to save on weight without sacrificing performance and while maximising beauty. This is not simply a show room bike. Dangerholm famously shreds his dream bikes pretty hard too.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.scott-sports.com/gb/en/sports/bike\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>Scott-Sports.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"e03d533013c7c19bc5d4c1471cf34ffca44b425a0251284cd224263a040a48ed","category":"Cycling"}